observations.recommendation:
We recommended that Management direct:

The MDRRMO to ensure the inclusion in the AIP/LDRRMFIP, under a separate caption, the list of projects and activities charged to the unexpended LDRRMF of previous years;

The Municipal Accountant to ensure that disbursements charged to LDRRMF – Special Trust Fund is supported with approved LDRRMFIP

We recommended that the:
CGSO:
take immediate and appropriate action on the above-mentioned properties and inform this Office of the action taken;
follow-up in writing the insurance claims of the two equipment that met an accident to recover or minimize any cost of repairs covered by the policy and furnish this Office, a copy of the letter duly received by the GSIS together with the reply, if any;
keep a complete and updated record of properties issued and take immediate action to repair and restore the properties to their usable condition upon discovery of the defect/damage and ensure that they are well-maintained while in storage to prevent further deterioration;
maintain monitoring for repairs and maintenance for each property, indicating the date, cost, and nature of repairs done on each property;
develop operating standards to be implemented within the agency to guard PPE against the improper or wasteful use of supplies or property, which shall be approved by the local sanggunian concerned; and
City Accountant:
include the checklist of supporting documents for repairs and maintenance, a document which indicates the repair history as required under Item 9.1.3.4 of COA Circular 2012-001, dated June 14, 2012.

We recommended that the:
City Engineer inspect the structures’ stability to ensure their safety, durability, and functionality, considering that both were already exposed to outside elements for more than nine (9) years, which can cause untimely deterioration and damage;
City Engineer recommend to Management, if it is found that these structures are still durable, the completion or improvement to lessen losses or wastage of government resources;
City Tourism Officer communicate with the TIEZA, inform the project's status, follow up if there is any additional fund allotted to finish the project as announced by the Chief Operating Officer of TIEZA, and ask for information regarding its formal turnover to the City of Bislig, if necessary; and
for future transactions, Local Chief Executive impose a policy that the project be implemented in accordance with the stipulations stated in the MOA to avoid delays or non-completion of projects due to possible increased costs and potential conflicts with the agreement.

We recommended that Management;

Direct the City Engineer to submit monthly to the City Accountant a report containing the list of completed projects, together with the necessary supporting documents such as Certificate of Completion, in order to better facilitate the recording of transfers of completed projects; and

Instruct the City Accountant to draw adjusting journal entries (AJEs) to correct the accounts affected. See proposed AJE in the attached Annex C-1.

We recommended and Management agreed to direct the:

Municipal Treasurer to prepare a schedule of unreleased/unclaimed checks at the end of the reporting period and submit thereafter to the Municipal Accountant, and;


Municipal Accountant to post adjustment in the books of accounts that correspond to the unreleased or unclaimed checks at every end of the reporting period.

We recommended that Management:

a.	Direct the immediate posting of all contracts awarded for Emergency Procurement under Republic Act (RA) No. 11469 (Bayanihan to heal as One Act) in the GPPB online portal;

b.	Direct Provincial Budget Office and Provincial General Services Office to be aware of any circulars/memorandum/advisories of the Government Procurement Policy Board (GPPB) with the reporting or posting requirements in relation to government procurement;

c.	Direct the Provincial Budget Office and Provincial General Services Office to coordinate and relay relevant information as necessary; and

d.	Henceforth, strict compliance to any circulars/memorandum/ advisories of the Government Procurement Policy Board (GPPB).

