Management Comment –
21.13	The leakage noted underneath the soil embankment was an effect of the 6.7 magnitude earthquake and aftershocks in February 2017.   Immediate remedial measures were introduced, such as: installation of hollow blocks wall and/or fence and leachate box in order to direct the flow of leakage waste water; additional soil embankment and compaction purposely to raise its higher elevation and stop the leaking; and installation of canal drainage along the perimeter of cell site in order to direct the flow of run-off water.  With regard to the discharged of leachate, City ENRO has undertaken the installation of two filtering box and monitoring pond.  Sampling test of waste water will be requested to Environment and Management Bureau Region 13.  Once the results of sampling test will pass the standards, discharge waste water will be engaged immediately.
